11:59.568 --> 12:01.536
What we do is
we move the shooting gallery.

12:01.604 --> 12:02.821
That seems to be
their biggest problem.

12:02.905 --> 12:04.272
Maybe that will make them happy.

12:04.340 --> 12:05.807
Check back in
with news Channel 4.

12:05.875 --> 12:09.360
Number one in curse coverage.

12:09.445 --> 12:11.880
You know how Indians
call corn maize?

12:11.947 --> 12:15.283
This is why.
I never knew that.

12:15.334 --> 12:17.502
Oh, my God.
I'm gonna go look by myself.

12:17.586 --> 12:19.370
Hey, are you all right?

12:19.455 --> 12:21.856
You seem super not happy.

12:21.924 --> 12:23.258
I'm fine.

12:23.325 --> 12:24.542
Oh, I forgot to tell you.

12:24.627 --> 12:26.694
I might be going
to Venezuela tomorrow.

12:26.762 --> 12:27.712
Forever.

12:27.797 --> 12:30.131
You're not fine.

12:30.182 --> 12:32.600
Ludgate, something is
upsetting you.

12:32.668 --> 12:35.534
Why don't you just go ahead
and tell me what it is.

12:35.654 --> 12:37.739
I'm not mad at Andy.
Andy's great.

12:37.807 --> 12:39.691
I awesome sauce Andy.

12:39.775 --> 12:41.676
April! Where are you?

12:45.197 --> 12:46.681
Look left.

12:46.749 --> 12:47.816
Look right.

12:47.883 --> 12:49.367
Yeah, okay.

12:49.451 --> 12:51.536
I don't know what's sicker,
me or your body.

12:51.620 --> 12:53.221
You aren't sick.

12:53.289 --> 12:54.889
Maybe you should
check out my abs.

12:54.957 --> 12:56.057
Are you experiencing
abdominal pain?

12:56.125 --> 12:58.209
Every day at the gym.

12:58.294 --> 12:59.878
- Ew.
- Feel.

12:59.962 --> 13:04.249
Oh.

13:04.333 --> 13:05.567
What are you doing tonight?

13:05.634 --> 13:07.886
I think I'm gonna have to pass.

13:07.970 --> 13:10.088
Your loss.

13:12.141 --> 13:14.309
- Are you gonna hit that?
- Him?

13:14.376 --> 13:17.345
He isn't exactly
boyfriend material.

13:17.396 --> 13:19.063
Who said anything
about a boyfriend?

13:19.148 --> 13:23.685
Use him, abuse him, lose him.

13:23.736 --> 13:25.553
Hey, hey, hey.
Did you find him?

13:25.604 --> 13:27.856
Yeah, Jerry.
He's right here in my pocket.

13:27.923 --> 13:30.158
Damn it.
Ground mission failed.

13:30.225 --> 13:34.028
We need a bird's eye view.

13:34.079 --> 13:36.030
You want me to climb
on top of the ferris wheel?

13:36.098 --> 13:39.066
We're extremely confident
that there's no curse.

13:39.118 --> 13:40.869
And everyone's gonna have
a great time tomorrow.

13:40.920 --> 13:41.936
Okay?

13:42.004 --> 13:44.122
Wow, first Ice Town.
Now this.

13:44.206 --> 13:46.207
Bad luck really
follows you around, huh?

13:46.258 --> 13:48.910
Okay, I'd like to
start by addressing

13:48.978 --> 13:51.462
some of the false
rumors about the festival.

13:51.547 --> 13:54.582
First of all,
we have plenty of food.

13:54.633 --> 13:55.884
There's no food shortage.

13:55.951 --> 13:57.635
There are not,
as one reporter suggested,

13:57.720 --> 14:01.105
dozens of escaped convicts
meandering around the carnival.

14:01.190 --> 14:04.642
And, at no time was
any Parks Department quote,

14:04.727 --> 14:06.461
"feasting on
petting zoo animals."

14:06.528 --> 14:09.096
You were in charge of

14:09.148 --> 14:10.315
watching a tiny horse,
and you failed.

14:10.399 --> 14:12.901
Look, I'm only
gonna say this once.

14:12.952 --> 14:16.304
What if Li'l Sebastian
is on this ferris wheel?

14:16.372 --> 14:18.439
How about you
only say that never.

14:18.490 --> 14:20.608
Leslie, how big of a disaster

14:20.659 --> 14:23.945
will this be, on a scale of 9 to 10?

14:23.996 --> 14:26.180
It will not be a disaster.

14:26.248 --> 14:27.281
It will be a success.

14:27.333 --> 14:28.967
And I want to
let everyone know that,

14:29.051 --> 14:30.919
in an attempt to be sensitive
to our Wamapoke friends,

14:30.986 --> 14:34.255
we have moved the shooting
gallery, per their request.

14:34.306 --> 14:35.690
So, yes, Perd?

14:35.758 --> 14:38.026
Yeah, the statement that
this reporter has is a question.

14:38.093 --> 14:40.461
Will that be enough
to lift the curse?

14:40.529 --> 14:44.182
Perd, you know as well as I do
that there no such...

14:44.266 --> 14:46.467
Oh, my God.

14:46.518 --> 14:49.203
Crap on a spatula.

14:49.271 --> 14:50.672
It's the curse.

14:50.739 --> 14:52.106
That's exactly what it is.

14:52.157 --> 14:53.308
You know what?
It is the curse.

14:53.375 --> 14:55.209
Wait, everyone, relax, please.

14:55.277 --> 14:56.811
We'll get this up
and running in no time.

14:56.862 --> 14:57.996
- Oh.
- Whoa!

14:58.080 --> 15:00.848
- Jerry, what the hell?
- I didn't do this.

15:00.916 --> 15:03.284
Jerry's fault.
Jerry's fault.

15:03.335 --> 15:05.954
Jerry's fault!
Jerry's fault!

15:06.005 --> 15:08.823
God.
I cannot catch a break.

15:08.874 --> 15:09.924
Yeah, well, I'll help you out.

15:09.992 --> 15:11.092
- I'm gonna go.
- What?

15:11.159 --> 15:12.210
I think I'm jinxed or something.

15:12.294 --> 15:13.962
What are you talking about?

15:14.013 --> 15:15.964
Look, you were totally fine
until I got involved.

15:16.031 --> 15:18.016
So I feel like I should
probably just go, okay?

15:18.100 --> 15:19.734
I'm really sorry.

15:19.802 --> 15:21.602
I'm the curse, I think.

15:21.670 --> 15:23.838
So I'm gonna, I'm gonna,
I'm gonna get out of here. All right?

15:27.045 --> 15:30.259
If they're missing this long,
they're usually dead.

15:30.379 --> 15:31.198
Well, if that's true,

15:31.199 --> 15:32.266
then you're gonna have to answer

15:32.334 --> 15:33.834
to the whole town.
And God.

15:33.902 --> 15:36.103
Okay, you were the one
who let him out, Tom.

15:36.154 --> 15:38.272
Okay?
Now stop trying to blame me.

15:38.340 --> 15:40.474
Jerry, can you please be quiet?

15:40.542 --> 15:43.711
I can't hear myself
not talking to Andy.

15:43.778 --> 15:45.713
Ron, will you please
tell me why April is mad at me?

15:45.780 --> 15:46.880
Ron, can you please tell Andy...

15:46.948 --> 15:48.782
All of you, be quiet!

15:48.850 --> 15:51.719
Andy, she's mad because
you said "awesome sauce"

15:51.786 --> 15:53.187
instead of,
"I love you, too."

15:53.254 --> 15:55.723
April, he loves you.
Stop being a child.

15:55.790 --> 15:57.991
Tom, you're clearly
at fault here.

15:58.059 --> 16:00.527
Blaming Jerry won't save you.

16:00.595 --> 16:02.796
Jerry, we both know you were
shotgunning funnel cakes

16:02.864 --> 16:05.465
instead of watching
Li'l Sebastian.

16:05.517 --> 16:08.001
So everyone apologize
to everyone else!

16:08.069 --> 16:10.037
- I'm sorry, Tom.
- I'm sorry, Jerry.

16:10.105 --> 16:11.038
- I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

16:11.106 --> 16:13.574
I do love you.

16:13.641 --> 16:15.642
You do?

16:15.694 --> 16:17.861
Yeah.

16:17.946 --> 16:21.248
That's what makes
the sauce so awesome.

16:25.036 --> 16:26.486
Aw, Jerry just farted!

16:26.538 --> 16:28.822
I'm very upset, I get nervous.

16:28.890 --> 16:31.508
Hey, Leslie.

16:31.593 --> 16:32.710
Generator's shot.

16:32.794 --> 16:34.661
No! I got the TMK-2500

16:34.729 --> 16:36.764
specifically for
the extra capacity.

16:36.831 --> 16:38.499
Wow, you know your stuff.

16:38.566 --> 16:39.633
You single?

16:39.684 --> 16:41.902
Not now, Ed.
How could that happen?

16:41.970 --> 16:44.438
All those TV crews
plugged in and overloaded it.

16:44.506 --> 16:46.306
Okay, how and where
can I get a new one?

16:46.357 --> 16:48.108
In, like, I don't know, now?

16:48.176 --> 16:50.778
There's only one place in town
that has a generator that size.

16:50.845 --> 16:53.614
You've gotta be kidding me.

16:53.681 --> 16:56.583
So...You need
to borrow a generator.

16:56.651 --> 16:59.153
Ken, I'm coming
to you on my knees.

16:59.220 --> 17:00.821
Begging for help.

17:00.889 --> 17:02.990
Much like the
early settlers of Pawnee

17:03.057 --> 17:04.358
begged the Wamapoke
200 years ago.

17:04.425 --> 17:06.059
- Ah, but that was...
- A trick.

17:06.127 --> 17:08.060
And over 50 Wamapoke
were slaughtered.

17:08.128 --> 17:09.096
I know.

17:09.164 --> 17:10.580
But this is not a trick.

17:10.665 --> 17:12.733
I am prepared to put
the Wamapoke history exhibit

17:12.800 --> 17:14.367
inside the carnival grounds.

17:14.435 --> 17:16.703
Right past
the entrance turnstile.

17:16.755 --> 17:19.473
So that you have to look at it
before you start having fun.

17:19.540 --> 17:21.141
Hm, now that's interesting.

17:21.209 --> 17:24.394
It's been really
awesome looking at you.

17:24.479 --> 17:27.146
Most carnival nurses
are total grenades.

17:27.214 --> 17:28.182
Okay, you're all set.

17:28.233 --> 17:30.918
You are free to go.

17:30.985 --> 17:35.305
Or you could stay here
and make out with h me

17:35.390 --> 17:36.774
until the lights come back on.

17:36.858 --> 17:38.442
Oh, hell yeah.

17:38.526 --> 17:40.978
Beat it, Donna.

17:41.062 --> 17:45.098
Aye, aye, captain.

17:45.166 --> 17:47.000
I'm just trying to do
something good for this town.

17:47.068 --> 17:49.369
And I'm trying to
save my friends' jobs.

17:49.437 --> 17:50.838
Can you help me out here?

17:50.905 --> 17:54.074
A native American tribe making
a deal with the government.

17:54.142 --> 17:56.543
Heh! What could go wrong?

17:56.611 --> 17:58.278
You can have
the generator, Leslie.

17:58.329 --> 17:59.296
Thank you, Ken.

17:59.380 --> 18:00.464
And I'll issue a statement

18:00.548 --> 18:02.850
saying that the curse
has been lifted.

18:02.917 --> 18:04.852
Actually, I have another idea.

18:22.353 --> 18:24.905
With that sacred ceremony,

18:24.972 --> 18:26.607
the Wamapoke curse
has been lifted.

18:30.478 --> 18:33.747
Wow, thank you.
Intense stuff from Ken Hotate.

18:33.814 --> 18:36.983
And in other good news,
he gave us a scare,

18:37.035 --> 18:38.335
but he's back now.

18:38.419 --> 18:41.021
The one, the only,
Li'l Sebastian!

18:47.795 --> 18:49.296
We spotted him from
the top of the ferris wheel

18:49.347 --> 18:51.849
at the center of the corn maze.

18:51.933 --> 18:54.685
After the power came back on,
we went and got him.

18:54.769 --> 18:57.471
It took us four hours
to solve that maze.

18:57.522 --> 18:59.189
It took the horse 15 minutes.

18:59.274 --> 19:01.475
Jerry's still out there.

19:04.145 --> 19:06.346
I suppose I oughta
go look for him.

19:06.397 --> 19:10.701
Right after I get a bratwurst.

19:16.708 --> 19:19.910
♪ ♪

19:19.994 --> 19:22.713
♪ Well, she was
an American girl ♪

19:22.797 --> 19:24.364
Welcome.

19:24.415 --> 19:25.865
Come on in, have fun.

19:25.917 --> 19:27.334
Enjoy yourself, ladies.

19:27.402 --> 19:30.804
- Hey.
- Hey, look who's back.

19:30.871 --> 19:32.105
I'm sorry I left.

19:32.173 --> 19:34.841
I honestly felt like I was
cursed or something.

19:34.893 --> 19:36.143
Ice Town, and now this.

19:36.210 --> 19:39.146
Ice Town was a disaster.

19:39.213 --> 19:41.732
And it seems like it
was probably your fault.

19:41.816 --> 19:43.817
From what I can tell, you
mismanaged the hell out of it.

19:43.884 --> 19:46.086
Wow, why even say that already?

19:46.154 --> 19:47.154
But the point is, this project,

19:47.221 --> 19:48.555
this is as much
yours as it is mine.

19:48.606 --> 19:49.856
It's ours.

19:49.908 --> 19:52.859
And...it's gonna be really great.

19:52.911 --> 19:55.329
And I'm glad you're here.

19:55.396 --> 19:59.449
Well, thank you.

19:59.534 --> 20:01.451
- Is this the guy?
- Yes, this is him.

20:06.341 --> 20:08.091
Special Wamapoke ceremony.

20:09.294 --> 20:10.944
The curse has been lifted.

20:11.012 --> 20:13.931
- Oh, wow. Thanks.
- Yeah.

20:14.015 --> 20:16.099
Oh, gosh.
You're filthy.

20:16.184 --> 20:18.452
Go clean yourself up.
Try to look professional.

20:19.887 --> 20:24.257
Hello.

20:24.309 --> 20:26.693
Enjoy yourself.

20:26.761 --> 20:28.595
Hi. I like your necklace.

20:28.646 --> 20:29.596
Hi.

20:29.664 --> 20:33.066
♪ ♪

20:36.710 --> 20:38.478
Oh, my God.
He is just the best ever.

20:39.770 --> 20:41.521
You're the best ever.

20:41.588 --> 20:43.473
But he's a close second,
aren't you, Li'l Sebastian?

20:43.557 --> 20:46.059
He really is amazing.

20:46.126 --> 20:48.094
You finally get it now, right?

20:48.162 --> 20:53.700
Hello, he's fantastic.
I totally get it now.

20:53.767 --> 20:55.868
I don't get it.
At all.

20:55.936 --> 20:58.738
It's kind of a small horse.
I mean, what am I missing?

20:58.789 --> 21:01.541
Am I crazy?

21:01.608 --> 21:03.442
Hey, Ben, you just missed it.
He whinnied.

21:03.494 --> 21:04.877
Oh, yeah, no.
I totally heard that.

21:04.945 --> 21:05.953
It was great.

